\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'93Friends, Argive leaders and counsellors\'97\uc0\u8232 my spirit prompts me to speak. But will I say\u8232 something true or false? A sound beats in my ear,\u8232 fast-moving horses\'92 hooves. Perhaps, as we speak,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0640\u8232 Odysseus and mighty Diomedes are driving\u8232 sure-footed horses back from Trojans. But I fear,\u8232 in my anxious heart, that Achaea\'92s best\u8232 are in trouble from pursing Trojan forces.\'94\
