\'93Renowned Odysseus, great glory of Achaeans,\uc0\u8232 tell me how you two obtained these horses.\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0650\u8232 Did you sneak into that crowd of Trojans?\u8232 Or did you meet some god who gave them to you?\u8232 They\'92re astonishing, like rays of the sun.\u8232 I\'92m always going in among the Trojans,\u8232 and I claim I don\'92t malinger by the ships,\u8232 although I\'92m an old man for a warrior.\u8232 But I\'92ve never seen, never imagined\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[550]\u8232 horses like these. I think some god met you\u8232 and gave them to you. For cloud-gathering Zeus\u8232 loves both of you, as does bright-eyed Athena,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0660\u8232 daughter of aegis-bearing Zeus.\'94\
