\'93O Nestor, son of Neleus, great glory\uc0\u8232 of Achaeans, if a god wanted to,\u8232 he\'92d easily give even better horses,\u8232 for gods are much more powerful than us.\u8232 But these horses which you ask about,\u8232 old man, are from Thrace, new arrivals.\u8232 Brave Diomedes killed their master,\u8232 along with all twelve of his companions,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0670\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[560]\u8232 their finest men. There was a thirteenth killed,\u8232 a spy we captured near the ships, sent there\u8232 by Hector and the other haughty Trojans,\u8232 to scout around our camp.\'94{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://records.viu.ca/~johnstoi/homer/iliad10.htm#n2"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \strokec2 *}}\
Odysseus finished. Then he laughed with triumph,\uc0\u8232 driving the sure-footed horses past the ditch.\u8232 Other Achaeans came after him, rejoicing.\u8232 When they reached Diomedes\'92 well-constructed hut,\u8232 they tethered the horses with cut straps in the stall\u8232 where Diomedes\'92 own swift horses stood, munching\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0680\u8232 their sweet grain. Odysseus put the bloodstained loot\u8232 from Dolon into his ship\'92s stern, until they\'92d made\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[570]\u8232 an offering to Athena. Then the two men waded\u8232 into the sea, washed off their legs and necks and thighs,\u8232 removing all the sweat. Once the surf had taken\u8232 layers of sweat from off their skin and their hearts\u8232 had been refreshed, they stepped in shining tubs and bathed.\u8232 They washed, rubbing lots of smooth oil on themselves,\u8232 then sat down to eat. From the brimming wine bowl\u8232 they drew off sweet wine and poured libations to Athena.\
